    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-15T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-15T03:00:00-05:00" n="749"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d749">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/9199: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Sebastian</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-15T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 15, 1939—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 15—7:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. I have been invited along with other Chiefs of Mission to attend the victory
                    celebrations. As they are now expected to take place on the 19th and 20th I
                    propose unless otherwise instructed to leave here for Madrid Wednesday noon
                    stopping off at Burgos for discussions at the Foreign Office en route.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
